---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
	description: "End-to-end ServiceNow SPM implementation for Acme Corporation. Five phases, $1.55M portfolio, full demand governance lifecycle.",
	title: "Acme Corporation — ServiceNow SPM Implementation",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>

  <!-- Back link -->
  <a href="/projects/" class="text-xs text-muted hover:text-accent transition-colors mb-12 inline-block">← All projects</a>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="mb-12">
    <p class="text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Case Study · ServiceNow SPM · May 2026</p>
    <h1 class="title mb-4 leading-tight">
      How do you give a CEO visibility over $1.55 million of strategic investment she currently can't see at all?
    </h1>
    <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
      This is the story of building a complete Strategic Portfolio Management implementation
      on ServiceNow — from blank PDI to executive dashboard — for a fictional company called Acme Corporation.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Meta strip -->
  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-8 gap-y-2 text-xs text-muted mb-12 pb-8 border-b border-dashed border-muted/30">
    <span><span class="text-global-text font-semibold">Platform</span> · ServiceNow Australia Release</span>
    <span><span class="text-global-text font-semibold">Instance</span> · dev375412.service-now.com</span>
    <span><span class="text-global-text font-semibold">Implementer</span> · Abdul Hadi Sheikh, CSA · CIS-SPM</span>
    <span><span class="text-global-text font-semibold">Status</span> · <span class="text-accent">Complete</span></span>
  </div>

  <!-- ACT 1: THE PROBLEM -->
  <section class="mb-14">
    <p class="text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">Act I — The Problem</p>

    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Acme Corporation is a mid-sized IT services company. 500 employees. Three major initiatives running simultaneously.
      A cybersecurity expansion. A cloud migration. A new ServiceNow consulting practice.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Combined budget: <span class="text-accent font-semibold">$1,550,000</span>. Combined visibility for the CEO: zero.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
      No single view of active projects. Resources double-booked across teams. A board requesting a quarterly roadmap
      that nobody could produce. Demand arriving from every direction with no process to separate strategic priorities from noise.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8">
      Most organizations don't fail at execution because their people are incompetent. They fail because strategy and
      execution live in different systems — or no system at all.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-2 mb-6">
      {[
        { label: "Cybersecurity Expansion", budget: "$500,000", pct: 32 },
        { label: "Cloud Infrastructure Migration", budget: "$750,000", pct: 48 },
        { label: "ServiceNow Consulting Practice", budget: "$300,000", pct: 20 },
      ].map(p => (
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm">
          <span class="w-52 flex-shrink-0 text-xs">{p.label}</span>
          <div class="flex-1 h-1.5 bg-muted/10 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
            <div class="h-full bg-accent rounded-full" style={`width: ${p.pct}%`}></div>
          </div>
          <span class="text-xs text-accent font-mono w-20 text-right">{p.budget}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm pt-2 border-t border-muted/20">
        <span class="w-52 flex-shrink-0 text-xs font-semibold">Total Portfolio</span>
        <div class="flex-1"></div>
        <span class="text-sm text-accent font-mono font-bold w-20 text-right">$1,550,000</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ACT 2: THE ARCHITECTURE -->
  <section class="mb-14">
    <p class="text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">Act II — The Architecture</p>

    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Before any demand was entered or any project created, the organizational foundation had to exist.
      In ServiceNow SPM this means thinking in layers — and getting the layers right before anything else.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
      {[
        { layer: "Organizational", what: "Acme Corporation as the primary Business Unit. Five departments. Five cost centers. Everything financial rolls up here." },
        { layer: "Access Control", what: "Nine role-based groups. Zero direct role assignments. User → Group → Role — the only sustainable approach as a team grows." },
        { layer: "Strategic", what: "Three enterprise goals. One portfolio as the executive container. Three programs, each owned by a named manager, each linked to a goal." },
        { layer: "Governance", what: "Standardized demand intake. Scoring on Impact, Risk, and Strategic Priority. No project starts without a business case." },
        { layer: "Execution", what: "Projects created only from approved demands — never manually. Every project linked to program, portfolio, goal, and cost center." },
      ].map((l, i) => (
        <div class="flex gap-4 text-sm">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full border border-accent/30 flex items-center justify-center text-accent text-xs mt-0.5">{i + 1}</div>
          <div>
            <span class="font-semibold">{l.layer} layer. </span>
            <span class="text-muted">{l.what}</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="border border-muted/20 rounded-lg p-5 font-mono text-xs leading-loose overflow-x-auto bg-muted/5">
      <div class="text-accent font-semibold">Acme Corporation</div>
      <div class="text-muted ml-2">│</div>
      <div class="ml-2">└── <span class="font-semibold">Acme Strategic Portfolio 2026</span></div>
      <div class="text-muted ml-6">├── Cybersecurity Expansion · $500K · Sarah Ahmed</div>
      <div class="text-muted ml-10">├── Security Assessment &amp; Gap Analysis</div>
      <div class="text-muted ml-10">├── Endpoint Protection Implementation</div>
      <div class="text-muted ml-10">└── SOC Setup and Monitoring</div>
      <div class="text-muted ml-6">├── Cloud Infrastructure Migration · $750K · Ali Hassan</div>
      <div class="text-muted ml-10">├── Cloud Readiness Assessment</div>
      <div class="text-muted ml-10">├── Infrastructure Migration Phase 1</div>
      <div class="text-muted ml-10">└── Testing and Go-Live</div>
      <div class="text-muted ml-6">└── ServiceNow Consulting Practice · $300K · Maria Khan</div>
      <div class="text-muted ml-10">├── Practice Setup and Hiring</div>
      <div class="text-muted ml-10">├── First Client Acquisition</div>
      <div class="text-muted ml-10">└── Delivery Framework Development</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ACT 3: THE GOVERNANCE TEST -->
  <section class="mb-14">
    <p class="text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">Act III — The Governance Test</p>

    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
      The first test of any portfolio management system is not whether it can track projects.
      It is whether it can prevent the wrong projects from starting.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8">
      Before a single resource was allocated, the Zero Trust Security initiative went through a structured evaluation
      process that most organizations skip entirely. The result was a defensible, financially justified,
      strategically aligned project — not just a good idea from a senior manager.
    </p>

    <div class="border border-accent/25 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
      <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-6">
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted mb-1 font-mono">DMND0001101 → PRJ0010001</p>
          <h3 class="text-base font-bold">Zero Trust Security Implementation</h3>
        </div>
        <span class="text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-accent/15 text-accent border border-accent/20 flex-shrink-0">Approved</span>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-5 mb-6">
        {[
          { label: "Capital Expenditure", value: "$500,000" },
          { label: "Operating Expenditure", value: "$250,000" },
          { label: "Total Planned Cost", value: "$750,000" },
          { label: "Financial Benefit", value: "$1,500,000" },
          { label: "ROI", value: "100%" },
          { label: "Assessment Score", value: "65–70" },
        ].map(item => (
          <div>
            <p class="text-xs text-muted mb-1">{item.label}</p>
            <p class="text-sm font-mono font-semibold text-accent">{item.value}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="border-t border-muted/20 pt-5">
        <p class="text-xs text-muted mb-3">Assessment scores</p>
        <div class="space-y-2">
          {[
            { dim: "Business Value", score: 8 },
            { dim: "Strategic Priority", score: 9 },
            { dim: "Risk (lower is better)", score: 2 },
          ].map(s => (
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-xs">
              <span class="text-muted w-44 flex-shrink-0">{s.dim}</span>
              <div class="flex-1 h-1.5 bg-muted/10 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
                <div class="h-full bg-accent rounded-full" style={`width: ${s.score * 10}%`}></div>
              </div>
              <span class="text-accent font-mono w-8 text-right">{s.score}/10</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center text-xs mt-6">
      {["Draft", "Submitted", "Screening", "Qualified", "Approved → PRJ0010001"].map((stage, i, arr) => (
        <span class={`px-3 py-1.5 rounded border text-xs ${i === arr.length - 1 ? 'border-accent text-accent bg-accent/10' : 'border-muted/30 text-muted'}`}>
          {stage}
        </span>
      ))}
    </div>
    <p class="text-xs text-muted mt-3">Five stages. Each one a gate. The project exists because the business case earned it.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ACT 4: EXECUTION -->
  <section class="mb-14">
    <p class="text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">Act IV — The Execution</p>

    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
      PRJ0010001 was generated automatically from the approved demand. Not created manually.
      That distinction matters — it means the financial case, the strategic linkage, and the program
      ownership all carried forward without anyone having to remember to fill in a field.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-3 mb-8">
      {[
        { week: "Weeks 1–2", phase: "Security Assessment", tasks: "Security audit, gap analysis. Dependencies enforced — nothing starts before its predecessor completes." },
        { week: "Weeks 3–8", phase: "Implementation", tasks: "Endpoint protection, identity and access configuration. Two cybersecurity engineers, one cloud architect." },
        { week: "Weeks 9–12", phase: "SOC Setup", tasks: "Monitoring framework, incident response design. One SOC analyst. Final deliverable: operational security operations center." },
      ].map(p => (
        <div class="grid grid-cols-[80px_1fr] gap-4 text-sm border-l-2 border-muted/20 pl-4 py-1">
          <span class="text-xs text-muted font-mono pt-0.5">{p.week}</span>
          <div>
            <span class="font-semibold text-xs">{p.phase}. </span>
            <span class="text-muted text-xs">{p.tasks}</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
      The dependency chain is deliberate: Security Audit → Gap Analysis → Implementation → SOC Setup.
      You cannot start phase two without completing phase one. That is not overhead.
      That is the difference between a project and a plan.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ACT 5: EXECUTIVE DASHBOARD -->
  <section class="mb-14">
    <p class="text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">Act V — What the CEO Sees</p>

    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Phase 5 answers the CEO's actual question — not "what are we building" but "are we on track to meet our goals."
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3 mb-8">
      {[
        { value: "$1.55M", label: "Total Portfolio" },
        { value: "3", label: "Programs · All Green" },
        { value: "9", label: "Projects" },
        { value: "Real-time", label: "Reporting" },
      ].map(stat => (
        <div class="border border-muted/20 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
          <div class="text-lg font-bold text-accent font-mono">{stat.value}</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-muted mt-1">{stat.label}</div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
      The CEO no longer asks which project to fund next. The data answers that question before the meeting starts.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- RBAC -->
  <section class="mb-14">
    <p class="text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">The Access Model</p>

    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Seventeen users. Nine groups. Zero direct role assignments.
      Adding a new project manager takes one action: add them to the ACME Project Managers group. Everything else follows.
    </p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-xs border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-muted/20">
            <th class="text-left text-muted font-normal py-2 pr-6">Group</th>
            <th class="text-left text-muted font-normal py-2 pr-6">Key Roles</th>
            <th class="text-left text-muted font-normal py-2">Members</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-muted/10">
          {[
            { group: "Portfolio Leaders", roles: "it_portfolio_manager, itfm_admin", members: "John Smith" },
            { group: "Demand Managers", roles: "it_demand_manager, assessment_admin", members: "Lisa Wong" },
            { group: "Executive Viewers", roles: "business_stakeholder", members: "CEO, CFO" },
            { group: "Program Managers", roles: "it_program_manager", members: "Ahmed, Hassan, Khan" },
            { group: "Project Managers", roles: "it_project_manager, resource_user", members: "9 PMs" },
            { group: "Security Engineers ★", roles: "it_project_user, resource_user", members: "Lee, Wilson, Farooq" },
            { group: "Cloud Architects ★", roles: "it_project_user, resource_user", members: "Sharma, Carter, Malik" },
            { group: "SN Consultants ★", roles: "it_project_user, resource_user", members: "R.Khan, Ahmed, Hussain" },
            { group: "Resource Approvers", roles: "resource_manager, timecard_approver", members: "Robert Chen" },
          ].map(row => (
            <tr class="hover:bg-muted/5 transition-colors">
              <td class="py-2 pr-6 font-semibold">{row.group}</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-6 text-muted font-mono">{row.roles}</td>
              <td class="py-2 text-muted">{row.members}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="text-xs text-muted mt-3">★ Group Type: <code>pps_resource</code> — required for Resource Management Workspace. Most common SPM config mistake. Easiest to miss.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- BEFORE / AFTER -->
  <section class="mb-14">
    <p class="text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">The Delta</p>

    <div class="space-y-2">
      <div class="hidden sm:grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-wider px-4 mb-1">
        <span></span><span>Before</span><span class="text-accent">After</span>
      </div>
      {[
        { kpi: "Project Visibility", before: "0% — spreadsheet based", after: "100% real-time dashboards" },
        { kpi: "Strategic Alignment", before: "Best guess", after: "1:1 mapping to enterprise goals" },
        { kpi: "Resource Conflicts", before: "High — frequent burnout", after: "Managed — capacity planned" },
        { kpi: "Reporting Time", before: "3–5 days manual", after: "Instant self-service" },
        { kpi: "Demand Governance", before: "Ad hoc project starts", after: "Scored, assessed, approved" },
        { kpi: "Financial Visibility", before: "Unknown until quarter end", after: "Real-time CapEx vs OpEx" },
      ].map(row => (
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-1 sm:gap-4 text-xs border border-muted/15 rounded-lg px-4 py-3 items-center">
          <span class="font-semibold">{row.kpi}</span>
          <span class="text-muted">{row.before}</span>
          <span class="text-accent">{row.after}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- KEY LEARNINGS -->
  <section class="mb-14">
    <p class="text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">What This Taught Me</p>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      {[
        {
          title: "Governance before execution.",
          body: "The demand intake process is more important than any technical configuration. Organizations that skip scoring and strategic linkage build fast and deliver wrong. Every rogue project I've ever seen started because someone with seniority asked for it. The intake process is how you say no to that politely."
        },
        {
          title: "pps_resource is the detail that breaks implementations.",
          body: "Resource groups without this group type are invisible to the Resource Management Workspace. It's not in the obvious documentation. It's the kind of thing you only know if you've actually built it."
        },
        {
          title: "SPM is an organizational discipline, not a technology project.",
          body: "ServiceNow is the structural body that makes decisions visible and enforceable. But the decisions themselves — who approves demands, what goals everything links to, how resources are governed — have to exist before you open the platform. The technology amplifies your governance. It cannot replace it."
        },
        {
          title: "Architecture boundaries are design decisions, not failures.",
          body: "Phase 4 resource management here is role-based rather than fully automated. That was a deliberate choice given the PDI environment. Identifying what's out of scope and why is a sign of implementation maturity. Forcing an incomplete feature into production to look thorough is the opposite."
        },
      ].map(l => (
        <div class="border-l-2 border-accent/30 pl-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2">{l.title}</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-muted leading-relaxed">{l.body}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <div class="border-t border-dashed border-muted/30 pt-8 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-4">
    <div>
      <p class="text-xs text-muted">Implemented by</p>
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Abdul Hadi Sheikh</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-muted">ServiceNow CSA · CIS-SPM</p>
    </div>
    <div class="text-right">
      <p class="text-xs text-muted font-mono">ServiceNow Australia Release</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-muted font-mono">dev375412.service-now.com · May 2026</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <div class="mt-12 rounded-xl border border-accent/25 p-6">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2">Need this built in your organization?</p>
    <p class="text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
      I implement ServiceNow SPM end-to-end — demand governance, portfolio structure, access control, and the executive dashboard. Same approach, your portfolio.
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="mailto:magic.alive11@gmail.com?subject=ServiceNow%20SPM%20Implementation" class="text-xs px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-accent/15 text-accent border border-accent/30 hover:bg-accent/25 transition-colors font-semibold">Start a conversation →</a>
      <a href="/services/" class="text-xs px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg border border-muted/30 hover:border-accent hover:text-accent transition-colors font-semibold">All services</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12">
    <a href="/projects/" class="text-xs text-muted hover:text-accent transition-colors">← Back to all projects</a>
  </div>

</PageLayout>
